==English==
===Etymology===
French, from [[torche]] ‘wipe’ + [[cul]] ‘arse’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /tɔ:ʃ'ku:l/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|torchecul|torcheculs}}
# ''(obsolete)'' something used to wipe the backside after defecation; [[arse-wipe]]
#:*'''1993''': Then he must needs sit bare-arsed on his jordan, hand scooping sweat from his brow, and void much black nastiness.  His '''torchecul''' was yet another discarded page of his play. — Anthony Burgess, ''A Dead Man in Deptford''